Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the bus of the Student Agency near Padua, Italy, arises the question whether stewards and passengers can travel within the coach during the journey.
"If we want to strictly and formally respect the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," says the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the road to the coach.
The girl was at this moment unfortunately sitting next to the driver, on the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she has at her disposal two other seats.
However, the bus may have an accident or even a sudden brake, also when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is equipped with standing or not seats by virtue of its technical data sheet.
If this standing equipment is not approved, the passengers shall remain seated.
The Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing seats; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the director of Radim Jančura.
"This is a matter that we dealt with with the department and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got that passengers can go to the toilet during the trip provided they have their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no unambiguous legal interpretation of the steward role - there is no legal prescription for that role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement also prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The Road Transport Act only knows the term vehicle receiver; it does not define its rights and duties," adds with more ambiguity the spokesman Hanzelka.
Josef Pokorný, the head of the road vehicle traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law adequately addresses the problem.
"It depends on the fact that the coach has permission in its approval to offer standing places.
Everything is in there," he says.
Buses are divided into urban areas, where there are standing positions and a limited maximum speed, inter-city with standing positions and a higher authorized speed, and long-distance coaches without standing positions with the highest authorized maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
As on the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Hoúñn, expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"During regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of the service in the aircraft.
Neither is it safe when turbulence occurs and the air hostess can hit her head."
"Now, in the event that the bus would have braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards by internal requirements," he said and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not resolved.
Jančura is ready to abolish these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer steward services.
He's hiring two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their trade to be a risky trade.
"Nevertheless, as soon as I have the impression that this is a risky trade, I will delete it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper upon boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he says.
The safety concern is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexei Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We have no hostesses. We oppose them from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident," he said, a year ago, in Týden.cz.
A huge tragedy has happened.
A young hostess from the Plze+ region, who had been working for the company for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a flashing signal and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he approached it by his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but as far as the financial compensation is concerned, it also relies on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the Act, which has been being developed for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could clarify the movement of stewards aboard the bus.
"However, it did not reach any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile at the wheel," says expert Ho
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," concludes spokesman Hanzelka, stating that the control of the safety of buses is under the authority of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
