"Sangre de Mayo", the dared bet of Garci
Drawing on the stories of Benito Pérez Galdós, José Luis Garci recreates the famous Spanish battle against the French in "Sangre de mayo", which is the most ambitious film of his filmography with nearly 15 million euros in budget.
The filmmaker tried "to stage the many characters and illustrate the social analysis" which he has always admired in the work of the famous novelist, he explained today during the presentation of the film, with Quim Gutiérrez and Paula Echevarría at the head of the long list of actors.
The film lasting more than two and a half hours, "Sangre de mayo" will be released in the cinema next Friday, which will then become a television series for Telemadrid of more than four hours.
A great admirer of Galdós' literature, José Luis Garci assured himself that he had made with this film "a dream of a child" thanks to Esperanza Aguirre, who commissioned him three years ago to make a commemorative film for the two hundred years of May 2, Madrid, something he had always accepted when the story was based on national historical facts.
The 15 million euros provided by the Municipality of Madrid constitute for Garci a "unique opportunity" to reproduce with the appropriate decorations and clothing the atmosphere of "a Spain which was wrong leader for the fight, since, the struggle for independence led the people to rebellions during the reign of Ferdinand VII", he pointed out.
But the filmmaker regrets not having obtained funding as for the films "Captain Alatrist" or "The Ghosts of Goya" - more than double that obtained for "Sangre de mayo" - because he could not shoot some scenes written in a script signed by Horacio Valcárcel, with whom he collaborated for almost his entire career.
The director of "Volver a empezar" influenced his usual way of working, on the staging of the actors, with whom he has the habit of repeating before starting the filming and to whom he does not cast, since it seems to him "humilizing" and considers that "the role of the filmmaker is to go to the theatre and the cinema to keep himself informed".
Many actors in "Sangre de mayo" repeat in front of the camera, like Miguel Rellán, Carlos Larrañaga or Fernando Guillén Cuervo.
Four times candidate for the Oscar (he won one), Garci considers that the three candidate films that represent Spain this year at the Hollywood Academy, "Sangre de mayo", "Sept tables de billiard français" and finally the winner, "Les sunflowers blinds", are not representative of the young Spanish cinema, "which deserves to be better known", he said.
With this movie Garci doesn't expect a price.
"At first you think you're working for posterity, and then you realize that you're working for prosperity, and now you're just making an extra movie," Garci explains after more than 30 years of professional career.
